# Vercel Web Analytics Integration

Successfully integrated Vercel Web Analytics into the Connect Six React application.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Dependencies
- Added `@vercel/analytics@^1.6.1` package to project dependencies

### 2. Modified Files
- **src/App.jsx**: 
  - Added import for `Analytics` component from `@vercel/analytics/react`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the main return statement, right after the existing `<SpeedInsights />` component

### 3. Updated Lock Files
- **package-lock.json**: Updated with new dependency tree for @vercel/analytics

## Implementation Details

Following the Vercel Web Analytics documentation for React applications (create-react-app style), the `Analytics` component was integrated into the main App component. This component:
- Provides seamless integration with React
- Automatically tracks page views and visitor metrics
- Works alongside the existing SpeedInsights integration

The Analytics component is placed at the end of the component tree to ensure it loads after the main application content and doesn't block rendering.

## Verification

- ✅ Build completed successfully (npm run build)
- ✅ No new linting errors introduced (existing linting errors are pre-existing and unrelated to this change)
- ✅ Package dependencies properly updated

## Next Steps

Once deployed to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics tab)
2. After deployment, verify that `/_vercel/insights/view` requests appear in browser Network tab
3. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard after users visit the site
